WHY: GitHub Discussions API is GraphQL-only (no REST support).

IMPLEMENTATION:
1. Add graphql helper: src/github/graphql.py
   - execute_graphql(query, variables) -> dict
   - Endpoint: https://api.github.com/graphql
   - Auth: Bearer token (same GITHUB_TOKEN)

2. Add 4 modules following existing pattern:
   - src/github/list_discussions.py
   - src/github/get_discussion.py  
   - src/github/get_discussion_comments.py
   - src/github/list_discussion_categories.py

3. Register in server.py (4 new @mcp.tool)

GRAPHQL QUERY EXAMPLE:
query($owner: String!, $repo: String!) {
  repository(owner: $owner, name: $repo) {
    discussions(first: 20) {
      nodes { number, title, url, createdAt, author { login } }
    }
  }
}

REFERENCE CODE:
- Go: github/github-mcp-server:pkg/github/discussions.go
- Python: jasona7/mcp_github_discussions:mcp_github_server.py
